    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>

                <p>accept my best thanks for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> late favor &amp; be
                    assured I shall rejoice to subscribe to <persName ref="pe0280">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Philips</persName> plan of prints which I much
                    approve. you have given yourself vast pains about the <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0209">map</title></bibl>, which I trust <persName ref="pe0006">Bailey</persName> will profit of. Inclosed is a order for my
                        <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0019">Br. Zoology</title></bibl> the
                    new edition. If there is a <hi rend="underline">perfect</hi>
                    <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0141">Ballendine</title></bibl> Pray buy it
                    at the auction I wonder you never mention <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> is he alive; for I fear on his
                        acc<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> by reason of his ill health.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
